            <title>[HBASE-5462] [monitor] Ganglia metric hbase.master.cluster_requests should exclude the scan meta request generated by master, or create a new metric which could show the real request from client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5462</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have a big table which have 30k regions but the request is not very high (about 50K per day).&lt;br/&gt;
We use the hbase.master.cluster_request metrics to monitor the cluster request but find that lots of requests is generated by master, which scan the meta table at regular intervals.&lt;br/&gt;
It is hard for us to monitor the real request from the client, it is possible to filter the scanning meta table or create a new metric which could show the real request from client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
